&lt;p&gt;Derivnex is DRW’s institutional platform for on-chain OTC derivatives lifecycle management, built on the permissioned Canton Network using the DAML smart-contract model. The platform transforms matched OTC trades into private, versioned smart-contract state with cryptographic attestation and immutable auditability. Margin, settlement, novation, termination, and other lifecycle events are executed and recorded directly on ledger through tokenized transfers between counterparties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a technically exceptional and commercially minded CTO to lead the architecture, engineering, and strategic evolution of Derivnex as it scales into production institutional markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CTO will define and execute the technical vision for Derivnex, leading platform architecture, distributed systems engineering, smart-contract infrastructure, security, and operational resilience. This leader will work closely with trading, operations, legal, and external counterparties to build secure, scalable, regulator-ready market infrastructure for OTC derivatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the technical strategy, architecture, and engineering roadmap for the Derivnex platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee development of distributed ledger infrastructure and DAML smart-contract systems deployed on Canton.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build secure, scalable systems supporting real-time collateral, margin, settlement, novation, and lifecycle event processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead engineering, infrastructure, DevOps, and security teams delivering institutional-grade reliability and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with trading, operations, legal, and risk teams to translate OTC derivatives workflows into programmable on-chain infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive platform security, governance, operational resilience, and auditability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Derivnex externally with counterparties, partners, and industry stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of OTC derivatives and post-trade lifecycle management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of collateral management and settlement workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise in blockchain technology, distributed systems, and smart-contract infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
